cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with generating video sequences from a single image using unsupervised learning. The use of variational models and bi-directional flow fields also suggests that it may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper involves handling occlusion and warping artifacts, which are common in multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) research.
